                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When your memory settings are lower than your post filesize settings than you are not able to receive files which exceed the memory limit, as the posted data can not be received.\n\nYou can read this within PHP's manual within the php.ini directives:\n{quote}\nGenerally speaking, memory_limit should be larger than post_max_size. \n{quote}\n\nAnd when you switch off the memory limit (-1) then you will also not get an error triggered.",
